    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-28T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-28T13:00:00-05:00" n="824"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d824">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/20172</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Garrett</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laredo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-28T12:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1916, noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Conditions in Mexico are growing worse daily. The Villistas are rapidly gaining
                    in strength and activity and it looks like they would soon have control over
                    northern Mexico. Have received information that it is their intention to capture
                    Monterey in the near future. An attack on Nuevo Laredo is scheduled for January
                    first. Several important families closely connected with <hi rend="italic">de
                        facto</hi> Government arrived here yesterday, including the family of the
                    Governor of Coahuila and the widow of Jesus Carranza, which shows that the
                    Carranza authorities realize the gravity of the situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
